Aggressive filtering (10\% threshold) removes the majority of unique
phenotypes, substantially reducing discriminative power (nDCG@10:
0.847). Conservative filtering (1\% threshold) removes only extremely
rare terms while preserving 98.4\% of baseline utility.

\subsubsection{4.4.4 Combined Privacy
Mechanisms}\label{combined-privacy-mechanisms}

We evaluated the composition of multiple privacy mechanisms---the
configuration most likely to be deployed in practice.

